<paragraph id="267936C4FE44FF8FFF0AFD015DC6FC1D" blockId="4.[166,1225,687,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25">
Biology. In laboratory, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFDDAFD1E5F48FD5D" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[523,782,719,746]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al. (1975)</bibRefCitation>
studied and described all immature stages, and provided details on larval biology. The larvae are semi-aquatic predators, attacking principally freshwater snails such 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE44FF8FFD7FFCC15F7BFC9E" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[686,829,783,809]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lymnaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Lymnaeidae</taxonomicName>
living on the wet edge of aquatic habitats and also their egg masses (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFDEDFCE15F6EFCFD" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[572,808,815,842]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al., 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFCE3FCE15FACFCFD" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[818,1002,815,842]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Pupariation takes place outside of the snails on the wet margin of aquatic habitats or soil, and represents the overwinter stage (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFEA8FCA15E28FC3D" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[377,622,879,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al., 1975</bibRefCitation>
). This species is multivoltine (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFC03FCA15883FC3D" author="Knutson, L. V. &amp; Rozkosny, R. &amp; Berg, C. O." box="[978,1221,879,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref6499" refString="Knutson, L. V., Rozkosny, R., Berg, C. O. 1975. Biology and immature stages of Pherbina and Psacadina (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Acta Scientiarum Naturlium Academiae Scientiarm Bohemicae Brno, 9 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1975">Knutson et al., 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE44FF8FFF77FC415D33FC1D" author="Barendregt, A. &amp; Mortelmans, J. &amp; Zuijlen, J. W." box="[166,373,911,938]" pageId="4" pageNumber="25" pagination="37 - 46" refId="ref5916" refString="Barendregt, A., Mortelmans, J., Zuijlen, J. W. 2014. Slakkendodende vliegen van het genus Psacadina in Nederland en Belgie (Diptera: Sciomyzidae). Nederlandse Faunistische Mededelingen, 42, 37 - 46 [In Dutch]." type="journal article" year="2014">Barendregt, 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
